2020年全球GDP年增长率受疫情影响将降低0.2%左右几天前，新西兰渔民们把刚刚捕来的共100多吨大龙虾放生大海。
New Zealand fishermen released a total of more than 100 tons of lobster they had just caught into the sea a few days ago.
当地媒体报道，中国传统春节是新西兰龙虾出口最畅销的时候，但今年受新冠状病毒疫情影响，中国客户纷纷取消订单。
The traditional Chinese New Year was the best-selling lobster export season in New Zealand, but Chinese customers cancelled orders this year because of a new coronavirus outbreak, local media reported.
新西兰龙虾95%都出口到中国，疫情使新西兰龙虾产业遭受沉重打击。
The New Zealand lobster industry has been hard hit by the outbreak, with 95 per cent of its lobster exported to China.
这只是目前全球经济受新冠状病毒疫情影响的冰山一角。
This is only the tip of the iceberg of a new coronavirus epidemic affecting the global economy.
2月6日，美国知名研究机构IHS Markit发布的最新预测报告称，新型冠状病毒疫情对全球经济的影响将比2003年的SARS疫情更严重。
The impact of the new coronavirus epidemic on the global economy will be worse than the 2003 SARS outbreak, according to a new report released on February 6 by IHS Markit, a leading US research institute.
这份名为《新冠病毒防控，影响波及全球经济》（Impacts of Coronavirus Containment Effort Ripple Through Global Economy）的报告显示，如果当前中国采取的前所未有的防控措施坚持到2月底，并从3月初开始逐步放开，对全球经济产生的影响将集中在今年上半年。
The impact on the global economy would be concentrated in the first half of this year, according to a report by the Impact of Coronavir Containment Efffort Through the Global Economy, which is called The New Crown Virus Prevention and Control, Impact on the Global Economy.
IHS Markit是知名全球商业资讯服务的多元化供应商，在全球范围内为各行业和市场提供关键信息、分析和解决方案。
IHS Markit is a diverse provider of well-known global business information services, providing critical information, analysis and solutions to industries and markets worldwide.
其拥有超过5万名商业和政府客户，包括80% 的世界500强企业和全球领先的金融机构。
It has more than 50,000 business and government clients, including 80 per cent of the world's top 500 companies and the world's leading financial institutions.
经济影响将集中在上半年2003年“非典”（SARS）疫情发生时，中国还是世界第六大经济体，其GDP仅占世界的4.2%。
The economic impact will be concentrated in the first half of 2003, when the SARS epidemic occurred, when China was the world's sixth-largest economy, accounting for only 4.2% of world GDP.
现在，中国已成长为世界第二大经济体，占世界GDP的比例已达16.3%，仅次于美国。
China is now the world's second largest economy, accounting for 16.3 per cent of world GDP, second only to the US.
据国际货币基金组织（IMF）统计，2019年，中国对全球经济增长的贡献率达到39%。
According to the International Monetary Fund, China's contribution to global economic growth reached 39% in 2019.
路透社评论称，中国的经济规模正在扩大，与世界的联系也更加紧密。
China's economy is expanding and it is more connected to the world, Reuters commented.
这意味着，目前中国经济增长面临的任何压力，都会对全球经济造成比以往更严重的冲击。
That means any pressure on China's economic growth will have a more severe impact on the global economy than in the past.
IHS Markit在报告中指出，中国制造业增加值所占全球份额从2002年的6.7%上升到2019年的30.5%，中国高技术产品增加值所占全球份额从7.2%上升到26.3%。
The IHS Markit report notes that China's global share of MVA increased from 6.7 per cent in 2002 to 30.5 per cent in 2019, and that China's share of the global value added of high-tech products increased from 7.2 per cent to 26.3 per cent.
与2003年“非典”疫情相比，新冠病毒疫情对全球经济的负面影响将更大。
Compared with the SARS epidemic in 2003, the negative impact of the new crown virus epidemic on the global economy will be even greater.
报告预测，新型冠状病毒爆发的长期经济影响将主要取决于中国的管控措施。
The report predicts that the long-term economic impact of the new coronavirus outbreak will largely depend on Chinese controls.
如果当前中国采取的前所未有的防控措施坚持到2月底，从3月初开始逐步放开，由此产生的经济影响将集中在2020年上半年，一季度全球实际GDP将因此减少0.8%，二季度将减少0.5%。
If China's unprecedented control measures continue until the end of February and are gradually liberalized from the beginning of March, the economic impact will be concentrated in the first half of 2020, with real global GDP falling by 0.8% in the first quarter and 0.5% in the second.
在这种情况下，放眼2020年，新冠病毒疫情及其相关措施导致全球实际GDP减少0.4%。
In this context, looking ahead to 2020, the new cap virus epidemic and its associated measures will reduce global real GDP by 0.4%.
IHS Markit预计，在2021年，防控措施的解除将释放此前压抑的需求，这预计将促使全球实际GDP增加0.4%。
IHS Markit predicts that the removal of controls by 2021 will free up previously depressed demand, which is expected to boost real global GDP by 0.4 per cent.
报告的撰写者之一、IHS Markit首席国际经济学家Elisabeth Waelbroeck-Rocha在接受《中国新闻周刊》采访时介绍，报告中新冠病毒危机对经济的影响，是基于68个经济体的宏观经济模型估算出来的，中国也是这68个经济体之一。
In an interview with China News Weekly, Elisabeth Waelbroeck-Rocha, chief international economist at IHS Markit, one of the authors of the report, said the report's impact on the economy was based on macroeconomic models of 68 economies, including China.
“通过该模型，我们能够观察到这次疫情爆发的溢出效应，例如工厂关闭、私人消费下降等等，这些溢出效应预计将持续几个星期。
"Through this model, we can observe the spill-over effects of the outbreak, such as plant closures and declining private consumption, which are expected to continue for several weeks."
”实际上，疫情防控对工业生产、固定投资、出口和进口都产生了影响，还引发了相应的政策反应，也都考虑在报告的分析、测算范围中。
Indeed, the epidemic's impact on industrial production, fixed investment, exports, and imports has triggered policy responses, all of which are considered in the report's analysis and measurement.
报告认为，新冠病毒疫情的影响在家庭消费方面最为明显，在工业方面稍微和缓，因为这一时期刚好赶上工厂季节性地闲置。
The report found that the impact of the new crown virus epidemic was most pronounced in household consumption, with some moderation in industry, as the period coincided with seasonal plant inactivity.
彼得森国际经济研究所高级研究员Gary Clyde Hufbauer也对《中国新闻周刊》表示，新冠病毒疫情比SARS影响更大，原因是新冠病毒在人与人之间的传染性更强，因此，检疫型措施的力度大得多，对经济的影响也就大得多。
Gary Clyde Hufbauer, a senior fellow at the Peterson Institute for International Economics, also told China News Weekly that the new crown virus is more contagious than SARS because quarantine measures are much more intense and have a much greater impact on the economy.
“不但旅游业受到严重影响，生活购物中心和体育活动场所的公共活动也会减少，雇佣了数千工人的工厂不得不采取特殊措施以避免传播。
"Not only will tourism be severely affected, but there will also be fewer public events at shopping malls and sports venues, and factories employing thousands of workers will have to take special measures to avoid spreading the disease.
”此外，由于新冠病毒的早期症状与普通感冒或流感的早期症状相似，出现这些症状的人都被隔离，影响范围更大。
Moreover, because the early symptoms of the new crown virus are similar to those of the early stages of a common cold or flu, people with these symptoms are isolated and have a greater impact.
Hufbauer认为，表示，2020年全球GDP年增长率受疫情影响将降低0.2%左右。
Hufbauer said annual global GDP growth in 2020 would be affected by the epidemic by about 0.2 per cent.
全球供应链被打乱据美国全国广播公司财经频道(CNBC)报道，2003年SARS造成的全球经济损失约为400亿美元，疫情造成的大部分经济损失其实“与病毒无关”，而是“与恐慌有关”。
Global supply chain disruption The global economic damage caused by SARS in 2003 was about $40 billion, with most of the damage being "virus-free" rather than "panic-related," according to NBC Finance and Economics.
彭博新闻社预计，新冠病毒对全球经济造成的冲击，可能是2003年SARS爆发的3至4倍。
Bloomberg News estimates that the impact of the new cap virus on the global economy could be three to four times greater than the SARS outbreak in 2003.
IHS Markit的报告指出，这次疫情有可能严重阻碍几个行业的发展，特别是汽车制造业。
The IHS Markit report says the outbreak has the potential to cripple several industries, particularly the auto industry.
因为中国宣布延长假期的11个省份，占中国汽车产量的三分之二以上。
China's 11 provinces, which have announced extended vacations, account for more than two-thirds of China's auto production.
如果这些企业停产至2月10日，预计疫情导致的第一季度产量损失约35万辆。
If the enterprises are shut down until 10 February, it is expected that the epidemic will result in the loss of approximately 350,000 vehicles in the first quarter.
如果这种情况持续到3月中旬，而邻近省份的工厂也处于停工状态，那么来自湖北的零部件短缺会造成中国范围内的供应链中断，可能会产生广泛的影响。
If this continues until mid-March, and factories in neighboring provinces are shut down, a shortage of spare parts from Hubei could disrupt China-wide supply chains, with potentially wide-ranging implications.
在这种情况下，第一季度的潜在减产将超过170万辆。
In that case, the potential first-quarter reduction would exceed 1.7 million vehicles.
作为此次疫情的重灾区湖北省，不仅集合着东风汽车、东风本田、神龙汽车、东风雷诺、上汽通用等多家汽车公司总部或生产工厂，更聚集了包括一批顶级供应商在内的零部件企业。
Hubei province, the epicenter of the epidemic, is not only home to Dongfeng Motor, Dongfeng Honda, Shenlong Automobile, Dongfeng Renault and SAIC General Motors, but also includes a group of top suppliers.
早在2月6日，华晨宝马就发布信息，宣布停工直至2月17日。
As early as February 6, morning BMW released a message announcing the shutdown of the work until February 17.
美国在华最大的汽车制造商通用汽车表示，将从2月15日起在中国恢复工厂生产。
General Motors, the largest US carmaker in China, said it would resume plant production in China from February 15.
丰田汽车发言人表示，截至1月29日，丰田决定暂停在华工厂的运营。
As of January 29, Toyota had decided to suspend operations at its China plant, a Toyota spokesman said.
此外，本田、日野、特斯拉、福特、东风汽车等也确认延迟复工计划。
In addition, Honda, Hino, Tesla, Ford, Dongfeng Motor also confirmed the delayed resumption plan.
受影响的不仅是设在中国的工厂。
It is not just factories based in China that are affected.
现代汽车在韩国的大部分工厂于2月7日暂停生产，起亚汽车也从2月10日起停工，因为中国的供应商无法继续提供相应零部件。
Most Hyundai's plants in South Korea suspended production on February 7, and Kia Motor stopped work on February 10 because Chinese suppliers could no longer supply the parts.
据了解，韩国进口线束中有87%是中国制造。
It is understood that 87% of the Korean imports are made in China.
欧洲的菲亚特克莱斯勒集团也表示，假如疫情仍未得到控制，其位于欧洲的工厂也面临因无法继续生产而暂时停工。
Europe's Fiat Chrysler Group also says its plants in Europe could temporarily shut down if the outbreak remains unchecked.
报告称，疫情所带来的石油需求不确定性还可能阻碍全球油价。
The report said uncertainty about oil demand from the outbreak could also hamper global oil prices.
2019年，中国的石油需求为每日13.9万桶，占全球市场的14%，而2003年为每日5.6万桶，只相当于全球需求的7%。
In 2019, China's oil demand was 139,000 barrels a day, accounting for 14 per cent of the global market, compared with 56,000 barrels per day in 2003, equivalent to only 7 per cent of global demand.
2019年，全球石油需求增长的一半来自中国，而在2003年，中国占世界石油需求增长的三分之一。
In 2019, half of the increase in global oil demand came from China, which accounted for a third of the increase in world oil demand in 2003.
同时，中国现在还是世界第二大进口国，占世界货物进口总量的10.4%，而2002年，这项占比仅为4.0%。
At the same time, China is now the world's second largest importer, accounting for 10.4 per cent of total world imports of goods, up from 4.0 per cent in 2002.
受疫情影响，2月3日，全球油价出现大跌，两大原油期货价格均跌至2019年1月以来的最低水平。
Affected by the outbreak, global oil prices fell sharply on February 3, with both crude oil futures prices at their lowest levels since January 2019.
从2月4日开始，石油输出国组织(OPEC)及其盟友正在不断评估新冠病毒疫情对全球石油需求的影响，讨论是否做出进一步减产的决定。
Since February 4, the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries and its allies are continually assessing the impact of the new crown virus epidemic on global oil demand and discussing whether to make a decision to cut production further.
世界贸易组织(WTO)的数据显示，在贸易方面，中国国内的需求不断增长，是石油、铁矿石和大豆等大宗商品以及集成电路等电子零部件的最大进口国。
Growing domestic demand for trade is the biggest importer of commodities such as oil, iron ore and soybeans, as well as electronic components such as integrated circuits, according to the World Trade Organisation.
这些商品的需求，可能会因为疫情导致的中国经济放缓而下滑。
Demand for these commodities is likely to decline as a result of the economic slowdown in China caused by the epidemic.
Elisabeth Waelbroeck-Rocha说，在IHS Markit的报告分析模型中，影响价格变化的一项主要因素是能源和大宗商品价格。
Elisabeth Waelbroeck-Rocha said that in the IHS Market report analysis model, one of the main factors influencing price changes was energy and commodity prices.
“作为大用户，中国国内暂停部分生产，减少对这类商品的进口，将对它们的出口国造成不利影响，这既是因为出口量下降，也是因为价格下跌。
"As a big user, China's domestic moratorium on some production and the reduction in imports of these commodities will have a negative impact on their exporters, both because of the decline in exports and because of the fall in prices."
疫情正是这样对中东和非洲这些能源生产国产生负面影响的，也影响到澳大利亚和拉丁美洲一些大宗商品出口大国。
That is how the epidemic negatively affects the energy-producing countries of the Middle East and Africa, as well as some of the major commodity exporters in Australia and Latin America.
目前估计，布伦特原油期货平均报价将下降至每桶55美元，而钢铁、铝和铜的价格则则将下降5%至7%。
It is now estimated that the average price of Brent crude oil futures will fall to $55 per barrel, while steel, aluminium and copper will fall by 5 to 7 per cent.
